= [[span class="bd"]]__RELEVANT TERMINOLOGY__[[/span]]
@@ @@
[[div class="oheader gray duplo large opaque"]]
[[span class="bd"]]##000|THE ASSIGNMENT ^^,,//(n.)//,,^^##[[/span]]
-----
##000|Database anomaly around which Deletions personnel manifest.## 
[[/div]]
[[div class="oheader gray duplo large opaque"]]
[[span class="bd"]]##000|THE BARRIER ^^,,//(n.)//,,^^##[[/span]]
-----
##000|Separation between timelines within the Database and the Gray. Abstract personnel, entities, and departments may traverse this delineation to various extents.##
[[/div]]
[[div class="oheader gray duplo large opaque"]]
[[span class="bd"]]##000|BLACKBOX ^^,,//(n.)//,,^^##[[/span]]
-----
##000|Junk data surviving from previous narratives which have been deleted.##
[[/div]]
[[div class="oheader gray duplo large opaque"]]
[[span class="bd"]]##000|CLUSTER ^^,,//(n.)//,,^^##[[/span]]
-----
##000|The minimum pre-defined space required to store a file. Also known as an //allocation block//.##
[[/div]]
[[div class="oheader gray duplo large opaque"]]
[[span class="bd"]]##000|THE DATABASE ^^,,//(n.)//,,^^##[[/span]]
-----
##000|The entirety of memoryspace from the perspective of Deletions agents; all timelines, plus the Gray.## 
[[/div]]
[[div class="oheader gray duplo large opaque"]]
[[span class="bd"]]##000|DELETION ^^,,//(n.)//,,^^##[[/span]]
-----
##000|The process of removing content from a file system's directory. The information those files contained still exists in memory until it is overwritten.## 
[[/div]]
[[div class="oheader gray duplo large opaque"]]
[[span class="bd"]]##000|ENTWINED TIMELINE ^^,,//(n.)//,,^^##[[/span]]
-----
##000|Atypical composite narrative structure with multiple "threads", often hinging on a particular character's choices.##
[[/div]]
[[div class="oheader gray duplo large opaque"]]
[[span class="bd"]]##000|EXTERNUS ^^,,//(n.)//,,^^##[[/span]]
-----
##000|Proposed space that is assumed to exist outside of the Database.##
[[/div]]
[[div class="oheader gray duplo large opaque"]]
[[span class="bd"]]##000|FRAGMENTATION ^^,,//(n.)//,,^^##[[/span]]
-----
##000|1. The process of breaking down data into small constituent parts, such as through partial overwrite.##

##000|2. The build-up of data fragments in a file system.## 
[[/div]]
[[div class="oheader gray duplo large opaque"]]
[[span class="bd"]]##000|GRAVEYARD ^^,,//(n.)//,,^^##[[/span]]
-----
##000|A nexus of deleted locations; a collection of //tombstones//.##
